reviewText:
Remember Assassin's Creed IV: Black Flag (ACIV)? Remember how cool it was to just explore that vast open world with your own ship? Well if you liked that BUY THIS GAME NOW.

Still not buying? Okay then... Read this review see if it changes your mind.

The gameplay is a lot like ACIV and Sid Meier's Pirates! and even a bit of Pixel Piracy but with some MMO elements. You can gather supplies and use 'em to lots of utilities. You can upgrade your ship and buy new ones, with better armor, speed, cargo capacity, and some other stuff too. You can also invest in 3 different sets of skills. Defense, Offence and Support, each with it's unique abilities and passive skills. You can even start your OWN settlements that later can turn into bigger towns. There are 4 main factions and 2 other mysterious ones, Each offers unique perks that can give you that edge you need.

NOTE: When I said it looked like ACIV I meant only the open world ship exploration and combat. Apart from that it has nothing to do with ACIV. I mean, ain't like you are gonna start doing parkour with a boat.

==============================================

PROS+ Extremely Addicting;
+ Fun Battles;
+ Well-Worked Skill System;
+ Customizable Sails and Ship Colors;
+ Good Economic System;
+ Customizable and/or Random World Generation;
+ MMO Elements.
+ You can also be a Pirate! (Y'arr!)
CONS- Menu interface needs just a BIT of improvement (like a back" button on the map creation would be good);
- Gameplay gets repetitive after some time;
- Mid and Late Game becomes a bit of a grinder;
- Needs more improvement on the Multiplayer.

==============================================

